03/03/2003
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- The Zagreb Law University, in co-operation with several foreign universities, launched a nine-day seminar on EU integration on Saturday (1 March). The forum will tackle economic, political and legal aspects of reforms. It attracted some 30 participants representing the European Council, civil servants and law students. A similar seminar took place in Rijeka, where several political parties gathered at the weekend for roundtable discussions on the EU accession process. They addressed institutional problems and reviewed the EU administrative structure in the fields of agricultural, structural and regional policies. (HINA - 02/03/03)
